In [37]:
def get_family_size_map(df, var):
    """
    Function to create family size categories, Alone, Small, Large
    
    input:
        df: Dataframe of your data
        Var: String, The feature you want to created
        
    output: 
        Categorize the size of the family
    """
    
    fam_dict = {}
    for size, pct in (df[var].value_counts(normalize = True) * 100).to_dict().items():
        if size == 1:
            fam_dict[size] = 'Alone'
        elif (size != 1) & (pct > 10.0):
            fam_dict[size] = 'Small'
        else:
            fam_dict[size] = 'Large'
    return fam_dict

# Create feature for titles

def get_title(name):
    """
    Function to create new feature for titles of people
    
    input:
        name: name of the person with a title
        
    output:
        Used with .pply(get_title) to obtain a new feature with the titles in it
    """
    title_search = re.search(' ([A-Za-z]+)\.', name)
    # if the title exists, extract it and return it
    if title_search:
        return title_search.group(1)
    return ''

        category.append('YA')
    elif age < 45:
        category.append('A')
    else: 
        category.append('E')

In [84]:
def my_confusion_matrix(y, y_hat):
    cm = confusion_matrix(y, y_hat)
    TN, FP, FN, TP = cm[0,0], cm[0,1], cm[1,0], cm[1,1]
    accuracy = round((TP+TN) / (TP+ FP+ FN+ TN) ,2)
    precision = round( TP / (TP+FP),2)
    recall = round( TP / (TP+FN),2)
    cm_labled = pd.DataFrame(cm, index=['Actual : 0 ','Actual : 1'], columns=['Predict : 0','Predict :1 '])
    print('\n')
    print('Accuracy = {}'.format(accuracy))
    print('Precision = {}'.format(precision))
    print('Recall = {}'.format(recall))
    print("-----------------------------------------")
    return cm_labled
